  "downloadSentinel": "Gastric Motility — Build Complete\n\nCore validation: Pathway A satisfied using Core Radiology: A Visual Approach to Diagnostic Imaging, 2nd edition, Nuclear and Molecular Imaging, “Esophageal and gastric motility,” pages 463–464. Core facts incorporated:\n\n- Tc-99m sulfur colloid or Tc-99m DTPA may be mixed with the ingested meal.\n- Standardized solid-meal gastric emptying imaging extends through 4 hours.\n- Normal residual gastric activity at 4 hours is <10% under the Core adult protocol.\n- Liquid gastric emptying may be studied with Tc-99m DTPA and normally occurs more rapidly.\n\nThe full Core section and complete RadPrimer article were reconciled. Pediatric thresholds, milk-study norms, dual-phase interpretation, acquisition details, technical pitfalls, and the 18 selected cases were derived from RadPrimer.\n\nFinal audit\n\n- Total user-provided cases: 18\n- Eligible for PRIMARY UNKNOWN: 18\n- Excluded: 0\n- PRIMARY UNKNOWN cards generated: 18\n- Differential Drills: 4\n- Definition cards: 2\n- Mechanism cards: 3\n- Boards Trap cards: 3\n- Epidemiology cards: 3\n- Other High-Yield cards: 16\n\nSECTION A cardinality check passed: 18 eligible cases correspond to exactly 18 PRIMARY UNKNOWN notes.\n\nTotal cards to export: 49\nExpected TSV lines: 49\n\nThe file contains exactly 22 tab-separated columns per line, no header row, no embedded physical newlines, blank Tags fields, source-basis summaries, verbatim supplied captions, and all required trigger-isolation checks.",
